  "doc_id": "26135",
  "text": "Phylogenetic trees were visualised using FigTree v1.4.2. A Bayesian clustering approach, implemented using the software STRUCTURE version 2.1 [CITATION_1] , was used to estimate the most likely number of clusters (K) into which the genotypes were assigned with certain likelihood. The population priors were not used, and a burn-in period of 50 000 iterations followed by 100 000 iterations was used. K was set from 1 to 10, and each run was replicated 25 times. The most likely number of clusters was identified by the delta K criterion with the STRUCTURE HARVESTER Web version 0.6.93 software (Earl and von Holdt, 2012) .",
